etymologies: late 17th century (as templet): probably from temple+ -et. The change in the ending in the 19th century was due to association with plate

definitions: a shaped piece of metal, wood, card, plastic, or other material used as a pattern for processes such as painting, cutting out, shaping, or drilling.
shortDefinitions: shaped piece of rigid material used as pattern for processes

definitions: something that serves as a model for others to copy

examples.text: the plant was to serve as the template for change throughout the company

shortDefinitions: something that serves as model for others to copy

definitions: a preset format for a document or file, used so that the format does not have to be recreated each time it is used
shortDefinitions: preset format for document or file

definitions: a nucleic acid molecule that acts as a pattern for the sequence of assembly of a protein, nucleic acid, or other large molecule

examples.text: secondary structure in the template strand is eliminated

shortDefinitions: nucleic acid molecule that acts as pattern for sequence of assembly of protein

definitions: a timber or plate used to distribute the weight in a wall or under a support.
shortDefinitions: timber or plate used to distribute weight in wall
